SQL-21

"Assume you're given the tables containing completed 
trade orders and user details in a Robinhood trading system.

Write a query to retrieve the top three cities that have the highest 
number of completed trade orders listed in descending order. 
Output the city name and the corresponding number of completed trade orders."

SELECT users.city,
  COUNT(CASE WHEN trades.status = 'Completed' THEN 1 END) AS total_orders
FROM trades 
JOIN users 
  ON trades.user_id = users.user_id
GROUP BY users.city
ORDER BY total_orders DESC
LIMIT 3;
